\c 34
\s1 Batas-Batas Tanah Kanaan
\p
\v 1 Tuhan berfiman kepadaku/Musa,
\v 2 “Katakanlah kepada orang Israel; Sebentar lagi kamu akan memasuki tanah Kanaan yang menjadi milik kalian/kamu. Inilah batas-batas wilayah tanah itu:
\v 3 Pada bagian selatan sampai ke pada gurun Zin, dekat perbatasan Edom sampai ke sebelah timur di mana perbatasan akan dimulai dari sdaerah selatan Laut mati.
\p
\v 4 Daerah itu akan diperluas sedikit ke bagian selatan dari padang gurun Zin dan sebelah selatan Kadesh-Bernea. Dari situ juga akan diperluas sampai ke Hazar Adar terus ke Azmon.
\v 5 Kemudian dari Azmon, akan diperluas lagi sampai ke Sungau Mezir dan berakhir di Laut Mediterania/Laut Tengah.
\p
\v 6 Batas sebelah barat adalah di Laut Mediterania/Laut Tengah.
\p
\v 7 Batas bagian utara dimulai dari Laut Mediterania/Laut Tengah sampai ke Gunung Hor.
\v 8 Dari sana terus ke Lebo-Hamat hingga berhenti/berakhir di Zadad.
\v 9 Sedangkan dari batas ke Zifron akan terus sampai berakhir di Hazar-Enan.
\p
\v 10 Sementara batas daerah/bagian Timur mulai dari Hazar-Enan sampai ke Sefam.
\v 11 Dari Sefam terus ke bagian timur Ain, kemudan turun ke Riblah, sampai sepanjang bukit-bukit di timur Danau Galilea.
\v 12 Selanjutnya batas itu turun ke sebelas selatan sepanjang Sungai Yordan dan berakhir di Laut Mati. Itulah
\p Those will be the borders around your country.”
\p
\v 13 So Moses/I \add told all that\add* to the Israeli people. Then he/I said to them, “That is the land that you will receive. You must throw ◄lots/stones that have been marked► to decide which area will go to each of the nine and a half tribes, because Yahweh has commanded that it should be divided among them.
\v 14 The tribes of Reuben, Gad, and half of the tribe of Manasseh have already received the land in which they will live.
\v 15 They have received land on the east side of the Jordan \add River\add*, across from Jericho.”
\p
\v 16 Then Yahweh said to Moses/me,
\v 17 “These are the men who will divide the land: First, Eleazar and Joshua.
\v 18 But other leaders \add from each of the twelve tribes will help them divide theland\add*.
\q1
\v 19-28 From the tribe of Judah, appoint Jephunneh's son Caleb.
\li1 From the tribe of Simeon appoint Ammihud's son Shemuel.
\li1 From the tribe of Benjamin appoint Kislon's son Elidad.
\li1 From the tribe of Dan appoint Jogli's son Bukki.
\li1 From the tribe of Manasseh appoint Ephod's son Hanniel.
\li1 From the tribe of Ephraim appoint Shiphtan's son Kemuel.
\li1 From the tribe of Zebulun appoint Parnach's son Elizaphan.
\li1 From the tribe of Issachar appoint Azzan's son Paltiel.
\li1 From the tribe of Asher appoint Shelomi's son Ahihud.
\li1 From the tribe of Naphtali appoint Ammihud's son Pedahel.”
\p
\v 29 Yahweh commanded that all those were the men who should divide the Canaan region among the Israeli people.